<h1>Mission</h1>

<p style="max-width:760px; line-height:1.7;">
The mission of the <strong>Journal of Revised Truths</strong> is to preserve and circulate memoranda addressing developments in human understanding across scientific, historical, and administrative domains.
</p>

<p style="max-width:760px; line-height:1.7;">
From time to time, conclusions that once appeared settled may warrant additional documentation. The Journal provides an archival venue for such memoranda when they emerge from institutional review, retrospective analysis, or the recovery of previously unavailable materials.
</p>

<p style="max-width:760px; line-height:1.7;">
The Journal does not seek to replace established historical records. Its purpose is to maintain a documentary trace of discussions that arise when those records are revisited.
</p>

<p style="max-width:760px; line-height:1.7;">
Where appropriate, memoranda are reproduced with their original circulation stage, administrative status, and known provenance.
</p>

<p style="max-width:760px; line-height:1.7;">
Certain conclusions may remain provisional.
</p>

</Layout>